newsitem.title: USA: August contracts expire quietly on CBOT soycomplex.
newsitem.headline: August contracts expire quietly on CBOT soycomplex.

text.p: August contracts for soybeans, soybean meal and soybean oil on the Chicago Board of Trade expired at midday amid little excitement, floor traders said.
"The shorts got out of August soybeans yesterday (Tuesday) and early this morning and it was very light trade into expiration," one floor trader said.
August soybeans settled at $8.17-1/4 a bushel, down 6-3/4 cents, August soymeal at $263.90 a ton, up $0.90 and August soyoil unchanged at 25.10 cents a lb.
